# Serial-Number Lookup Tools

These pages are top organic-traffic drivers on the site (e.g. `/kubota-serial-number-lookup` is currently #1). All edits must preserve rank signals and follow the established pattern.

## URL paths in use

- `/<brand>-serial-number-lookup` — canonical interactive tool page.
- `/brand/[slug]/serial-lookup` — brand-page tab that embeds the canonical tool via `SerialLookupEmbed` (do not duplicate logic; both surfaces share the same API).
- `/parts/construction-equipment-parts/<topic>` — long-form companion articles (the Bobcat one is the highest-converting of these). Link from articles to the interactive tool, not the other way around.

Never invent a 4th path for the same brand. Pick one URL as canonical and consolidate.

## Data tables (Supabase, public schema)

- `<brand>_plate_locations` — family-level + model-specific plate guidance.
- `<brand>_model_serial_ranges` — production-year windows + parts-catalog serial breaks.
- `<brand>_model_cues` — model-code → equipment-family mapping for the API regex.

Migrations enriching these MUST be additive, use `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING`, and add a unique index when one is missing. Cite public sources in `notes` columns. Reference: `supabase/migrations/20260516000000_enrich_kubota_lookup.sql`.

## API route contract (`/api/<brand>-lookup/route.ts`)

- Accept `{ serial, model? }`, return `{ input, parsed.family, plate.guidance[], serialRanges[], notes[] }`.
- When a model is provided, rank model-specific plate rows above family rows.
- When `serialRanges` is empty for a typed model, push an explicit "No published parts-book serial breaks were found for X — read the data tag for the PIN" note instead of leaving the result silent.

## Page contract

- **JSON-LD must be server-rendered** as raw inline `<script type="application/ld+json" dangerouslySetInnerHTML={{ __html: JSON.stringify(...) }} />`. **Do NOT use `next/script` with `strategy="afterInteractive"` for JSON-LD** — it ships after hydration and Google misses it on first crawl.
- Include `WebApplication`, `HowTo`, and `FAQPage` schemas.
- Include a visible `<details>`-based FAQ section that mirrors the `FAQPage` JSON-LD verbatim (matching content is required to avoid structured-data spam flags).
- After a successful lookup, render an in-result CTA linking to `/quote?equipment=<Brand>+<Model>&notes=PIN+/+serial:+<serial>` — `/quote` already accepts those URL params (canonical = `/quote`).
- Form labels must be bound to inputs via `htmlFor` / `id`.

## Do not change without explicit user approval

`metadata.ts` and `layout.tsx` (title, description, canonical, alternates, OG image) on any top-ranking lookup page. These are live SEO signals on revenue-relevant traffic.

## Canonical reference

`app/kubota-serial-number-lookup/page.tsx` + the migration above. Mirror that pattern for new brands.
